      "description": "The house graph $(3,1,2)$: 5 vertices, 6 edges, $L=2$, 5 external legs. Two trivalent vertices joined by chains of 3, 1, and 2 edges; this is the 'house' shape. Symanzik polynomials given in eq. eq:UVF213. Proposition p:house: for $D=4$ and generic kinematics $\\mathrm{Gr}^W_3 H^4(X_{(3,1,2);4};\\mathbb{Q}) = H^1(E)$ for an elliptic curve depending on kinematics and $\\mathrm{Gr}^W_4 H^4 = \\mathbb{Q}(-2)^r$. The order-8 Picard-Fuchs operator $L_{(3,1,2);4}$ factors as $L_3 L_1^2 L_1^3 L_1^4 L_2$ with the order-2 factor having normal form matching the Picard-Fuchs equation of the attached family of elliptic curves.",
